Aim of the script

The dataset used in this script was taken from Costanzo et.al. 2021 and used to calculate robusntess for each strain according to the formula in Trivellin et.al 2022

Load dataset

df <- read_excel("~/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-Chalmers/PhD/Experimental_Data/Robusntess application on existing dataset/raw data/Costanzo_et_al_Data_File_1_Conditions_Strains_Fitness.xlsx",

df[,6:19][is.na(df[,6:19])] <- 0

### changing genenames in df to match SAFE
df <- df %>% 
  separate(`Allele (Essential genes only)`, c("gene", "allele"), "-") %>%
  select(-`gene`) %>%
  unite('gene',`Gene Name`:`allele`, sep="-", remove=TRUE, na.rm = T)

Calculatin Robustness

Calculating mean and stdev for each strain

df_1 <- df %>% 
  mutate(mean = rowMeans(select(df, 5:18), na.rm = TRUE))
df_1$sd = apply(df_1[,5:18], 1, sd, na.rm=TRUE)

computing the Fano factor for each strain

df_R <- df_1 %>%
  mutate(R=-sd^2/mean)

normalizing the Fano factor for the mean value of the fitness across all strains

meanF <- mean(df_R$mean)

df_R_norm <- df_R %>%
  mutate(R_n=R/meanF)

plotting robusntess normalized and not normalized

df_long_R <- df_R_norm %>% 
  gather(key="robustness", value="value", c("R", "R_n")) 
# checking data distribution 
ggplot(df_long_R, aes(x = robustness, y = value)) + 
  geom_violin(trim = FALSE) +

intersection among strains with high fitenss and high robusntess

#isolating the 25th and 75th percentiles with best/worse fitness and best/worse robustness
best_90_F <- df_R_norm %>%
  filter(mean >= quantile(df_R_norm$mean, 0.90)) 

best_90_R <- df_R_norm %>%
  filter(R_n >= quantile(df_R_norm$R_n, 0.90)) 

worst_10_F <- df_R_norm %>%
  filter(mean <= quantile(df_R_norm$mean, 0.10)) 

worst_10_R <- df_R_norm %>%
  filter(R_n <= quantile(df_R_norm$R_n, 0.10)) 

venn <- list(High_Fitness=best_90_F$ID, High_Robustness=best_90_R$ID, Low_Fitness=worst_10_F$ID, Low_Robustness=worst_10_R$ID)
ggvenn(venn,fill_color = c("#922A2B","#E2C140", "#4775A5","#5B9589"), text_size = 8,set_name_size=10)

SAFE <- read_excel("~/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-Chalmers/PhD/Experimental_Data/Robusntess application on existing dataset/raw data/Costanzo_et_al_Data_File_2_SMF_Functional_enrichment.xlsx",

comparing the top robut strains with df2 to check in which process those genes/alleles are involved

topR_SAFE <- generics::intersect(best_90_R$gene, SAFE$`Gene/Allele`) #not all the best strains in the fitness dataset were associated with the SAFE datasaet as the ID was missing from the SAFE dataset
top_R_strains <- SAFE[SAFE$`Gene/Allele` %in% topR_SAFE,] #extract rows 
#working on a separate dataset for R0 and merging
topR0_SAFE <- generics::intersect(df_R_zero$`gene`, SAFE$`Gene/Allele`)
top_R0_strains <- SAFE[SAFE$`Gene/Allele` %in% topR0_SAFE,] #extract rows 
top_R_strains <- top_R_strains %>%
  rbind(top_R0_strains) %>%
  rename(SAFE_group = `SAFE network region`)

count_high_R_process <- top_R_strains %>%
  group_by(SAFE_group) %>%
  tally()

comparing the worst robut strains with df2 to check in which process those genes are involved

worstR_SAFE <- generics::intersect(worst_10_R$`gene`, SAFE$`Gene/Allele`)
worst_R_strains <- SAFE[SAFE$`Gene/Allele` %in% worstR_SAFE,] %>% #extract rows 
  rename(SAFE_group = `SAFE network region`)

count_low_R_process <- worst_R_strains %>%
  group_by(SAFE_group) %>%
  tally()

putting the four bubble plots together

add_ID <- function(df, ID) {
  df %>%
  arrange(desc(n))%>%
  slice(1:20) %>%
  mutate(ID = ID)
}

#extracting the first 5 overly represented processes
HR <- add_ID(count_high_R_process, "High Robustness")
LR <- add_ID(count_low_F_process, "Low Robustness")
HF <- add_ID(count_high_F_process, "High Fitness")
LF <- add_ID(count_low_F_process, "Low Fitness")

df_bubble <- HR %>%
  rbind(LR) %>%
  rbind(HF)%>%
  rbind(LF)

#plotting 
packing_tot <- circleProgressiveLayout(df_bubble$n, sizetype='area')
packing_tot$radius <- 0.95*packing_tot$radius
data_tot <- cbind(df_bubble, packing_tot)
dat.gg_tot <- circleLayoutVertices(packing_tot, npoints=50) 

# Plot 

data_tot$SAFE_group[is.na(data_tot$SAFE_group)] <- "unknown"

ggplot(data_tot, aes(area = n, fill = ID, label = SAFE_group, subgroup = ID)) +
  geom_treemap(colour = "white", size = 2)+
  geom_treemap_subgroup_border(colour = "white", size = 5) +
  geom_treemap_text(grow = T, reflow = T, colour = "white") +
  facet_wrap( ~ ID) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#922A2B","#E2C140","#4775A5","#5B9589"))+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
  labs(
    fill = "Group"
  ) +
  bbc_style()
